values.text: Ohhh! Don't worry! Every disease has its own cure!üòä

That's fine! As I'm unable to understand your conditions in detail, I'm gonna suggest you some useful tips, and tricks, and a short YouTube video. You may follow some of them. Those are clinically effective facts.

üíó Do something good for someone else, even though you may not want to. Do a favor, help them find something, give them an item that will help them in some way. Start the flow of positive energy.

 üíó Eat the best chocolate you can get your hands on. In bed. Or in the bath.

 üíó Turn up the music you really love. Play it so loudly that it soaks in through your skin. Dance in your pajamas. Feel the pain lift.

 üíó Have a romance in your head.

üíó  Buy a remote control for your camera & dip your toes into the pool of narcissism.

 üíó Call a friend & ask them if they want to have a slumber party.

 üíó Throw yourself head-first into a creative project. Something that you‚Äôre excited about but which feels a little too big for you. You‚Äôll be so consumed by it that it will fuel you for ages.

 üíó Do the splits. Or at least try. (Be gentle though!)

üíó  Sing. Loudly. Badly. Off-key. Whatever you like. It works. The last time I was on my way somewhere really nerve-wracking, I was in a cab. The radio was playing & I was so anxious that the only way I could distract myself was by singing along. Loudly. The driver probably thought I was a total nut but I didn‚Äôt care & it did the trick!

 üíó  Cover your entire body in cocoa butter & fall asleep.

 üíó  Drink 2 liters of fizzy drink (pop, soda, you know) & stay up until sunrise.

 üíó  Write a list of things that you appreciate right now, in the present moment. Focus on each of them & let the love inside you well up. Even when things appear to be going really, really badly, there are always things to be happy about. (That‚Äôs one of the reasons why we do Things I Love Thursday ‚Äî to help bring your attention back to the positive.)
